 group is organized based on its four main product groups roughly  of its revenue is generated by personal care products which include skin and hair care products deodorants and oral care products another nearly  comes from the food product segment which consist of snacks soups bouillons sauces margarines mayonnaise salad dressings and spreads refreshment products bring in nearly  of sales and include ice cream tea beverages weightmanagement products and nutritionally enhanced staples for sale in developing markets the home care product division brings in the remainder of revenue and consists of a variety of cleaning products powders liquids and capsules and soap bars financial performance following five years of sales growth unilever groups revenue in  fell by  to  billion with sales declines from all product segments twothirds of the drop was driven by a  decline food product sales mostly from lagging spread sales in the european and north american markets the groups refreshment product sales also fell by  further hurting the top line the companys personal care segment fell the least as its dove brand remained strong declining revenue caused the groups net income to drop by  to  billion after two years of profit growth in  and  operations provided  billion or  less cash than in  partly from lower earnings but mostly due to a combination of negative cash flows from working capital and from an elimination of profits from discontinued brand operations strategy to free up resources and focus them on growing divisions and product lines unilever group has made a series of brand divestitures in recent years in in  as part of its strategy of making foods fit for growth the company sold off its flailing wishbone skippy and unipro brands between  and  the company made a series of brand acquisitions to strategically expand its product portfolio buying alberto culver sara lee kalina and toni  guy mergers and acquisitions in  unilever acquired startup razor manufacturer dollar shave club for  billion in cash founded in  dollar shave club built its business selling inexpensive mens razors exclusively through digital commerce sites the acquisition bolsters unilevers presence in the online sales space the company traditionally sells its products through brickandmortar retailers where profit margins can be smaller  show less  show full description  show less  show full history  show less  show all competitors alticor inc avon products inc campbell soup company colgatepalmolive company conagra brands inc general mills inc johnson  johnson lvmh moet hennessy louis vuitton mars incorporated mondelez international inc revlon inc s c johnson  son inc the cocacola company the estee lauder companies inc the procter  gamble company  show less  show all company news and press releases unilever un q sales gain on currency and acquisitions nasdaq fri jul  unilever up  ytd with more to come seeking alpha fri jul  mccormick  company buys reckitt benckisers food division no bargain but not bad seeking alpha thu jul  buying growth bloomberg business thu jul  unilever h pretax profit rises underlying sales up   quick facts rttnews wed jul  mccormick to buy reckitt unit for bplus citybizlist tue jul  procter  gamble company pg exdividend date scheduled for july   nasdaq tue jul  axogen inc k  departure of directors or certain officers election of directors appointment of certain officers compensatory arrangements of certain officers us securities and exchange commission tue jul  unilever nv  halfyearly earnings release traders mon jul  industry welcomes asas tougher stance on gender stereotyping in ads but warns brands against recoiling to safe options the drum mon jul  wall streets ma chatter from july  dominion diamond unileverhormelreckitt he equipmentneff mobileyeintel benzinga mon jul  amazon files trademark to get into meal kits continuing to dominate blue apron the street sun jul  unilever and hormel are front runners in a deal to buy reckitt food uni